CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 9, 1941, pg. 3 reads: "James Weldon Johnson Camp Model Project - Above are scenes from Camp James Weldon Johnson, situated on Raccoon Creek in foothills of the beautiful Allegehney [Allegheny] mountains just 34 miles from Pittsburg. Some of the children who enjoyed the facilities of the spacious grounds during the past two weeks are pictured...Bottom left: View of the beautiful lake and piers with the lifeguard tower in the foreground.  The tower affords a clear and complete view of the swimming and boating area..."
TitMainTitle: Boys standing on wooden dock, at Camp Weldon Johnson with lifeguard tower, Beaver County, Pennsylvania
